<p><em>Last updated: 19 May 2026</em></p>

<p>This Privacy Policy describes how aira ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, stores, shares and protects personal information when you visit, use or make a purchase from aira-breathing.com (the "Site").</p>

<p>By using the Site, you agree to the practices described in this Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.</p>

<h2>1. Who we are (Data Controller)</h2>
<p>The data controller responsible for your personal information is:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Trading name:</strong> aira</li>
  <li><strong>Legal entity name:</strong> AIRA WELLNESS ECOM - FZCO</li>
  <li><strong>Registered address:</strong> Building A1, Dubai Digital Park, Dubai Silicon Oasis, Dubai, United Arab Emirates</li>
  <li><strong>Country of registration:</strong> United Arab Emirates</li>
  <li><strong>Commercial registration / Trade licence number:</strong> 85942</li>
  <li><strong>Contact email for privacy matters:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@shop-aira.com">contact@shop-aira.com</a></li>
</ul>
<p>If you have questions about this Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at the email above.</p>

<h2>2. What information we collect</h2>
<p>We collect personal information in three main ways:</p>

<h3>a) Information you give us directly</h3>
<p>When you create an account, place an order, sign up for our newsletter, or contact us, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Full name</li>
  <li>Billing and shipping address</li>
  <li>Email address</li>
  <li>Phone number</li>
  <li>Payment information (processed by our payment provider — see Section 5; we do not store full card numbers on our servers)</li>
  <li>Order history and product preferences</li>
  <li>Any messages, feedback or correspondence you send us</li>
</ul>

<h3>b) Information collected automatically when you browse</h3>
<p>When you access the Site, our hosting platform (Shopify) and our analytics tools automatically receive:</p>
<ul>
  <li>IP address and approximate location derived from it</li>
  <li>Device type, operating system and browser</li>
  <li>Referring URL and pages visited on the Site</li>
  <li>Date, time and duration of visit</li>
  <li>Cookie identifiers (see Section 7)</li>
</ul>

<h3>c) Information from third parties</h3>
<p>We may receive information about you from:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Payment processors (confirmation of payment status, fraud signals)</li>
  <li>Shipping and logistics partners (delivery status, address verification)</li>
  <li>Social media platforms, if you interact with our content or log in via a social account</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Why we use your information and the legal basis</h2>
<p>We only use your personal information for clearly defined purposes. The table below sets out each purpose and the legal basis under applicable data protection laws (including the GCC data protection laws applicable to us and, where relevant, the EU General Data Protection Regulation for customers in the EU/EEA).</p>

<div class="policy-table-wrap">
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Legal basis</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Process and fulfil your orders, including delivery and returns</td><td>Performance of a contract with you</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Verify your payment and prevent fraud</td><td>Legitimate interest in protecting our business and customers; legal obligation</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Send order confirmations and shipping updates</td><td>Performance of a contract with you</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Provide customer support and respond to your enquiries</td><td>Performance of a contract; legitimate interest</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Send marketing emails about new products, offers or content</td><td>Your explicit consent (you can withdraw at any time)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Improve the Site, our products and customer experience</td><td>Legitimate interest in improving our service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Comply with legal, tax and regulatory obligations</td><td>Legal obligation</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Defend our legal rights or respond to lawful requests by authorities</td><td>Legal obligation; legitimate interest</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<p>We do not use your personal information for automated decision-making that produces legal or similarly significant effects on you.</p>

<h2>4. Marketing communications and your choices</h2>
<p>We will only send you marketing emails if you have opted in. Each marketing email contains an unsubscribe link, and you can withdraw your consent at any time by:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Clicking "unsubscribe" at the bottom of any marketing email, or</li>
  <li>Emailing us at <a href="mailto:contact@shop-aira.com">contact@shop-aira.com</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Withdrawing consent does not affect the lawfulness of any processing carried out before you withdrew it. Even if you unsubscribe from marketing, we will still send you transactional messages relating to your orders (order confirmations, shipping notifications, etc.).</p>

<h2>5. Who we share your information with</h2>
<p>We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with the following categories of recipients, and only to the extent necessary:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Shopify Inc.</strong> — our e-commerce platform provider. Shopify hosts our Site and stores order and customer data on secure servers. Shopify's privacy practices are described at <a href="https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">shopify.com/legal/privacy</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Payment processors</strong> — to process your payment securely. Card data is encrypted and handled in accordance with PCI-DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard). We do not store full payment card numbers.</li>
  <li><strong>Shipping and fulfilment partners</strong> — to deliver your order to the address you provide.</li>
  <li><strong>Email and communication providers</strong> — to send order confirmations and, where you have opted in, marketing communications.</li>
  <li><strong>Professional advisors</strong> — accountants, lawyers and auditors, bound by confidentiality.</li>
  <li><strong>Government authorities and regulators</strong> — where we are required by applicable law, court order, or to protect our legal rights.</li>
  <li><strong>Successor entity</strong> — if aira is sold, merged or undergoes a corporate reorganization, your information may be transferred to the new owner under the same protections set out in this Policy.</li>
</ul>
<p>Each third-party service provider is contractually required to handle your data securely and only for the purposes we instruct.</p>

<h2>6. International transfers of your data</h2>
<p>Some of our service providers (including Shopify) are based outside the GCC, including in jurisdictions such as the United States, Canada, the European Union and Ireland. When we transfer your data internationally, we ensure adequate protection by relying on one or more of the following:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The country has been recognized as providing adequate protection by the relevant authority</li>
  <li>Standard contractual clauses or equivalent contractual safeguards</li>
  <li>Your explicit consent, where appropriate</li>
</ul>
<p>You can request more information about the specific safeguards in place by emailing <a href="mailto:contact@shop-aira.com">contact@shop-aira.com</a>.</p>

<h2>7. Cookies and tracking technologies</h2>
<p>A cookie is a small text file placed on your device when you visit a website. We use cookies and similar technologies to make the Site work, to understand how it is used, and (where you consent) for marketing.</p>
<p>The cookies we use fall into four categories:</p>

<h3>Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
<p>Required for the Site to function. These cannot be disabled.</p>
<div class="policy-table-wrap">
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>_session_id</code></td><td>Allows Shopify to manage your session</td><td>Session</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>_secure_session_id</code></td><td>Secure session management</td><td>Session</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cart</code></td><td>Stores the contents of your cart</td><td>2 weeks</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>storefront_digest</code></td><td>Authentication for password-protected stores</td><td>Indefinite</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h3>Performance and analytics cookies</h3>
<p>Help us understand how visitors use the Site.</p>
<div class="policy-table-wrap">
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>_shopify_visit</code></td><td>Tracks number of visits</td><td>30 minutes from last visit</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>_shopify_uniq</code></td><td>Counts unique visitors</td><td>Until midnight of the following day</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h3>Functional cookies</h3>
<p>Remember preferences such as your selected currency (used for currency conversion based on your IP-derived location).</p>

<p>You can manage cookies through your browser settings or, where applicable, via the cookie consent banner on the Site. Disabling strictly necessary cookies may break parts of the Site.</p>

<h2>8. How long we keep your data</h2>
<p>We keep your personal information only as long as we need it for the purposes set out in this Policy, or to meet legal, accounting or reporting obligations.</p>
<p>Indicative retention periods:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Account and order data:</strong> for the duration of your customer relationship with us, plus the period required by applicable tax and commercial law.</li>
  <li><strong>Payment transaction data:</strong> stored only as long as needed to complete the transaction, then deleted by the payment processor (subject to their own legal retention obligations).</li>
  <li><strong>Marketing consent records:</strong> until you withdraw consent, plus a short period to evidence the withdrawal.</li>
  <li><strong>Website analytics:</strong> typically up to 26 months.</li>
  <li><strong>Customer support correspondence:</strong> typically 3 years after the matter is resolved.</li>
</ul>
<p>When the retention period ends, we securely delete or anonymise your data.</p>

<h2>9. Your rights</h2>
<p>Subject to the data protection law applicable to you, you have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
  <li><strong>Right of rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
  <li><strong>Right of erasure ("right to be forgotten")</strong> — ask us to delete your data where there is no compelling reason for us to keep it</li>
  <li><strong>Right to restrict processing</strong> — ask us to limit how we use your data</li>
  <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
  <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests, including direct marketing</li>
  <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> — at any time, where processing is based on consent</li>
  <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> — with the relevant data protection authority in your jurisdiction (for example, the UAE Data Office, the Saudi Data and Artificial Intelligence Authority (SDAIA), or your local equivalent)</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:contact@shop-aira.com">contact@shop-aira.com</a>. We will respond within the timeframe required by applicable law (typically 30 days). We may need to verify your identity before fulfilling your request.</p>
<p>There is no fee for exercising your rights, unless your request is manifestly unfounded or excessive.</p>

<h2>10. Security</h2>
<p>We take the security of your data seriously. Measures we have in place include:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Encryption of data in transit using TLS (SSL) and at rest using industry-standard encryption (AES-256 where applied by our providers)</li>
  <li>PCI-DSS compliant payment processing handled by certified payment gateways</li>
  <li>Access controls limiting who can view personal data internally</li>
  <li>Use of reputable third-party providers (Shopify, payment processors) that maintain their own security certifications</li>
</ul>
<p>No method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, but we follow industry best practice. In the event of a personal data breach that is likely to affect your rights, we will notify you and the relevant authority in accordance with applicable law.</p>

<h2>11. Children's privacy</h2>
<p>The Site is not directed to children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are under 18, please do not use the Site or provide any personal information. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child without verified parental consent, we will delete that information.</p>
<p>By using the Site you confirm that you are at least 18 years old, or that you have the consent of a parent or legal guardian.</p>

<h2>12. Links to other websites</h2>
<p>The Site may contain links to third-party websites. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those websites. We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of third parties. We encourage you to read the privacy policy of any third-party site you visit.</p>

<h2>13. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements or for other operational reasons. The "Last updated" date at the top of this Policy indicates when it was most recently revised.</p>
<p>If we make material changes, we will notify you by email (where we have your address) or by posting a prominent notice on the Site before the changes take effect.</p>

<h2>14. Contact us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, would like to exercise your rights, or wish to make a complaint, please contact us at:</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@shop-aira.com">contact@shop-aira.com</a><br><strong>Postal address:</strong> Building A1, Dubai Digital Park, Dubai Silicon Oasis, Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
